# Project Conventions

> Reading list, key constraints, and project overview are in `AGENTS.md` (always applied). This rule adds naming and coding conventions not covered there.

## Naming

- **Event names:** kebab-case, namespaced with feature ID. `"rss:new-entry"`, `"todo:item-completed"`.
- **Action/query names:** kebab-case. `"mark-read"`, `"get-entries"`.
- **Feature IDs:** lowercase kebab-case slugs. `"rss-reader"`, `"todo"`, `"pomodoro"`.

## Path Aliases

- `@core/*` → `src/core/*`
- `@shell/*` → `src/shell/*`
- `@features/*` → `src/features/*`

Configured in both `tsconfig.json` and `vite.config.ts`.

## Skills

Check `.agents/skills/` for domain-specific guidance (Electrobun, etc.). See `specs/SKILLS.md` for the full skills guide.
